Name: Fabulous Wet Burritos
Description: Flour tortillas are filled with a mixture of ground beef, refried beans, and chiles then topped with a generous amount of sauce and cheese.
Author: Cindy Newell

Name: Cheesy Amish Breakfast Casserole
Description: This hearty casserole has bacon, eggs, hash browns, and three different cheeses all baked into a comforting breakfast dish, perfect for feeding a crowd.
Author: parothstein

Name: Chipotle Chicken
Description: Smokey chipotle peppers make an intense marinade for chicken cooked with sour cream and tender baby spinach.
Author: Bethany Gorski

Name: Chef John's Cauliflower Pizza Crust
Description: Enjoy all the flavor of delicious pizza, but with a cauliflower crust!
Author: Chef John

Name: Pressure Cooker Barbeque Chicken
Description: This quick and easy chicken recipe uses a pressure cooker to yield moist, flavorful chicken with barbeque sauce in under 30 minutes.
Author: CatherineSolo

Name: Waistline-Friendly Turkey Chili
Description: Chipotle barbeque sauce, lime juice, and ground cumin flavor this colorful chili.
Author: Kate

Name: Whole Earth Kale Salad
Description: Cooled cooked brown rice adds texture to this hearty salad packed with kale, cabbage, and carrots.
Author: CookMe2

Name: Banana Frittata
Description: Here's a quick and easy banana pancake recipe that anyone can make.
Author: nausheen

Name: Mamaw's Chicken and Rice Casserole
Description: Chicken and rice casseroles are a staple of American cooking. This version uses cream of mushroom, cream of celery, and cream of chicken to give a rich flavor to a quick school-night dinner when getting your back-to-school routine settled.
Author: katiefbenham

Name: Ooey Gooey Chili Mac Lasagna
Description: Cheese dip, lasagna noodles, chili, and Cheddar cheese are layered and baked into this ooey gooey chili mac lasagna, a comfort food mash-up.
Author: Leslie Kelly

Name: Steel-Cut Oats and Quinoa Breakfast
Description: Steel-cut oats and quinoa breakfast cereal with almond meal, flax, and cinnamon is a quick and easy vegan meal to start the day with.
Author: AnneP

Name: Cheesy Sausage Lasagna Soup
Description: This cheesy tomato-based soup with Italian turkey sausage, sliced mushrooms, and fresh spinach tastes just like lasagna in a bowl.
Author: cookinme

Name: Slow Cooker Peach Upside Down Cake
Description: Peaches caramelize with brown sugar in the bottom of your slow cooker for a warm, gooey upside-down cake.
Author: cupcakeproject

Name: Stef's Slow Cooker Creme Brulee
Description: Turn your slow cooker into an oven-water bath and all-to make super-easy, decadent desserts like this creme brulee.
Author: cupcakeproject

Name: Hearty Beef Lasagna Soup
Description: This beef lasagna soup with fusilli and Parmesan cheese is a quick and easy weeknight meal you probably have all the ingredients for!
Author: Mommy For Two

Name: Warm Berry Compote
Description: Cook frozen berries with orange juice in your slow cooker for a yummy dessert by itself or over ice cream.
Author: cupcakeproject

Name: Slow Cooker Peanut Butter Fudge Cake
Description: Warm fudge and peanut butter make for a sweet, scoopable cake straight from the slow cooker. This is great served over vanilla ice cream, too!
Author: cupcakeproject

Name: Triple Coconut Cake
Description: If you like coconut, this super moist slow-cooker cake is sure to please (three times over)!
Author: cupcakeproject

Name: Slow-Cooked Chicken Drumsticks
Description: In this super easy recipe, seasoned chicken drumsticks are cooked low and slow in a 250-degree oven until the meat falls off the bone.
Author: cheftini

Name: Raghavan's Curry Blend
Description: Try this easy blend in place of curry powder for brighter flavors.
Author: Raghavan Iyer

Name: Raghavan's Garam Masala
Description: Heat these easy-to-find ingredients for an aromatic addition to Indian dishes.
Author: Raghavan Iyer

Name: Super Simple Raita
Description: This yogurt-y condiment goes perfectly with spicier dishes, and takes just a few minutes to toss together. You can use either fresh fruit or veggies.
Author: Raghavan Iyer

Name: Baked Chicken Drumsticks (Asian Fusion)
Description: Chicken drumsticks are baked in a fusion mix of ginger, hoisin sauce, and canned peaches to create this Asian-inspired main dish for a crowd.
Author: Eve Ivanka

Name: Honey Garlic Chicken Wraps
Description: Your kids will love these simple honey garlic chicken wraps filled with rice and raw carrots that are quick and easy to make on a weeknight.
Author: LELIZABETHS

Name: Honey Garlic Sauce
Description: This thick garlic and ginger sauce sweetened with honey and brown sugar is a great topping for chicken wing or meatball appetizers.
Author: Rachel

Name: The Best Homemade Honey Garlic Sauce
Description: This family recipe for homemade honey garlic sauce is easy to make with 5 ingredients and complements meat and vegetables equally well.
Author: Belinda M

Name: Sriracha Honey Chicken Legs
Description: Baked chicken legs are tossed in a sweet and spicy mix of honey, butter, and sriracha sauce in this low-carb weeknight dish full of flavor.
Author: Nicole

Name: Sriracha Honey Salmon
Description: Sriracha sauce and honey team up in this broiled salmon dish packed with sweet and spicy flavor that makes a simple, delicious dinner for 2.
Author: klhn1986

Name: Quinoa Breakfast Cereal
Description: Quinoa gets the breakfast treatment in this hot cereal recipe made with apricots, almonds, and flax seeds that's a nice change from oatmeal.
Author: laur_218
